.TH "Response.blob" "JS" "October 8, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Response.blob \- Response: blob() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]blob()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]Response\f[R]
interface takes a \f[CR]Response\f[R] stream and reads it to completion.
It returns a promise that resolves with a \f[CR]Blob\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
blob()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] If the \f[CR]Response\f[R] has a
\f[CR]Response.type\f[R] of \f[CR]\[dq]opaque\[dq]\f[R], the resulting
\f[CR]Blob\f[R] will have a \f[CR]Blob.size\f[R] of \f[CR]0\f[R] and a
\f[CR]Blob.type\f[R] of empty string \f[CR]\[dq]\[dq]\f[R], which
renders it \f[I]useless\f[R] for methods like
\f[CR]URL.createObjectURL()\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
A promise that resolves with a \f[CR]Blob\f[R].
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]DOMException\f[R] \f[B]AbortError\f[R]
The request was aborted.
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown for one of the following reasons:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
The response body is disturbed or locked.
.IP \[bu] 2
There was an error decoding the body content (for example, because the
\f[CR]Content\-Encoding\f[R] header is incorrect).
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
In our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/tree/main/fetch/fetch-request
fetch request example
.UE \c
\ (run \c
.UR https://mdn.github.io/dom-examples/fetch/fetch-request/
fetch request live
.UE \c
), we create a new request using the \f[CR]Request()\f[R] constructor,
then use it to fetch a JPG.
When the fetch is successful, we read a \f[CR]Blob\f[R] out of the
response using \f[CR]blob()\f[R], put it into an object URL using
\f[CR]URL.createObjectURL()\f[R], and then set that URL as the source of
an \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element to display the image.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myImage = document.querySelector(\[dq]img\[dq]);

\f[B]const\f[R] myRequest = \f[B]new\f[R] Request(\[dq]flowers.jpg\[dq]);

fetch(myRequest)
  .then((response) \f[B]=>\f[R] response.blob())
  .then((myBlob) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    \f[B]const\f[R] objectURL = URL.createObjectURL(myBlob);
    myImage.src = objectURL;
  });
.EE
